# QA Journal - WI-AC-040 (open-source-local-runtime: Postgres-only persistence)

## Test Date
2026-07-09

## Work Item
WI-AC-040

## Environment
- API running on PORT=3099 (maps to causeflow-api container port 5171)
- Env: OSS runtime (CAUSEFLOW_RUNTIME=oss)
- Auth: Local JWT via /v1/auth/register + /v1/auth/login
- Infrastructure: Docker compose with causeflow-postgres, redis, hindsight, causeflow-api, causeflow-worker
- No ministack, no langfuse, no DynamoDB

## Verification Results

### Part 1: Postgres is the only persistence layer
- Health endpoint returns `{"postgres":"ok","redis":"ok","anthropic":"skipped","queues":"ok"}` — no dynamodb check registered
- Boot logs show: "Using Postgres repositories (OSS runtime)", no DynamoDB reference
- ✅ PASS

### Part 2: 31 tables in causeflow schema
- `psql` via docker exec against causeflow-postgres: `SELECT count(*) FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema = 'causeflow'` returns 31
- Table names: api_keys, approvals, audit_entries, billing_accounts, change_events, chat_messages, evidence, feedback, hypotheses, incidents, integrations, invites, notifications, oauth_tokens, package_dependencies, patterns, remediation, repo_nodes, repo_service_maps, runbook_registry, service_edges, service_nodes, slack_notifications, slack_oauth_states, tenants, tool_calls, triggers, usage_records, user_settings, users, widget_sessions
- ✅ PASS

### Part 3: POST /v1/incidents with auth writes to Postgres
- Registered via POST /v1/auth/register: received JWT token
- Created incident via POST /v1/incidents with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`: returned 201 with incidentId
- Verified row in Postgres: `SELECT * FROM causeflow.incidents WHERE tenant_id = $1` shows the created incident with title, severity, description
- Note: route is at `/v1/incidents` not `/api/v1/incidents` as documented in AC (minor documentation drift, no functional impact)
- ✅ PASS

### Part 4: No DynamoDBClient/DocumentClient instantiation at boot
- In OSS mode, `getDynamoClient()` returns `createOssStubClient()` — a plain object without calling `new DynamoDBClient()`
- The `new DynamoDBClient({})` path is in the `else` branch (AWS runtime) never reached in OSS mode
- No `DocumentClient` usage anywhere in the codebase
- DynamoDB health check is NOT registered in OSS mode
- ✅ PASS

## Defects
None. All acceptance checks pass.

## Verdict
integration=true, implementation=true, qa=true

