# QA Journal - WI-AC-042 (open-source-local-runtime: local auth replaces Clerk)

## Test Date
2026-07-09

## Work Item
WI-AC-042

## Environment
- File audit against branch `plan/opensource-docker` (no server started)
- CAUSEFLOW_RUNTIME=oss code path

## Verification Results (Static Code Audit)

### Requirement 1: POST /v1/auth/register returns 201 with {user, tenant, token}
- ✅ Handler in `oss-auth.routes.ts` POST `/register` mounted at `/v1/auth`
- ✅ Creates tenant via `PgTenantRepository.create()` and user via `PgUserRepository.create()`
- ✅ Password hashed with scrypt (timing-safe), stored in user JSONB data column via `pgUpdate`
- ✅ JWT signed with `SignJWT` from `jose` using `config.auth.jwtSecret` (reads JWT_SECRET env)
- ✅ Returns 201 with `{ user: {id, email, name}, tenant: {id, name, slug}, token }`

### Requirement 2: POST /v1/auth/login returns fresh JWT; wrong password returns 401
- ✅ Handler in `oss-auth.routes.ts` POST `/login` mounted at `/v1/auth`
- ✅ Retrieves user by email via `PgUserRepository.findByEmail()`
- ✅ Loads password hash from Postgres JSONB, verifies with `scryptSync` + `timingSafeEqual`
- ✅ Returns JWT on success, 401 `{"error":"Invalid email or password"}` on mismatch

### Requirement 3: GET /v1/whoami returns user and tenant
- ✅ Route at `GET /v1/whoami` in `app.ts`
- ✅ Reads from middleware context set by `auth.middleware.ts`
- ✅ Returns `{ user: {id, email}, tenantId, role, roles }`

### Requirement 4: JWT signed with JWT_SECRET, verified with jose locally
- ✅ Signing: `oss-auth.routes.ts` uses `SignJWT` with HS256, `config.auth.jwtSecret`
- ✅ Verification: `auth.middleware.ts` OSS path uses `jwtVerify` from `jose` with same secret
- ✅ Claims match: `sub`, `email`, `tenant_id`, `roles`, issuer=`causeflow`, audience=`causeflow-api`
- ✅ Default dev secret when JWT_SECRET unset: `'dev-secret-DO-NOT-USE-IN-PRODUCTION'`

### Requirement 5: Clerk webhook endpoint removed from running code path
- ✅ `app.ts` mounts `ossAuthRouter` (OSS routes) when `config.isOss()`, not Clerk auth.routes
- ✅ The `POST /clerk-webhook` endpoint in `auth.routes.ts` is never mounted in OSS mode
- ✅ `handle-clerk-webhook.usecase.ts` is only dynamically imported in the AWS runtime branch

### Requirement 6: clerk-client removed from running code path
- ✅ `clerk-client.ts` is lazily initialized (no `createClerkClient` call at module load)
- ✅ Imported via `create-invite.usecase.ts` but `getClerkClient()` is never called in OSS mode
- ✅ `sendClerkInvitation` wraps errors gracefully
- ✅ Bootstrap comment explicitly notes the dynamic import pattern avoids pulling in @clerk/backend

### Requirement 7: ClerkUserEmailResolver removed from running code path
- ✅ Bootstrap sets `userEmailResolver = undefined` when `config.isOss()`
- ✅ `ListAuditEntriesUseCase` handles undefined resolver gracefully

### Requirement 8: Tenant isolation (AC-010) holds for OSS-issued tokens
- ✅ JWT contains `tenant_id` as a signed claim (HS256), cannot be tampered with
- ✅ `auth.middleware.ts` reads `tenant_id` from verified JWT, sets it on request context via `tenantId()` branded type
- ✅ All Postgres repositories scope queries by `tenant_id` (every table has `tenant_id NOT NULL`)
- ✅ Cross-tenant reads impossible — tenant comes from signed JWT claim, never from request params

